text:
Twenty Third Ave., east side, between Cropsey and Warehouse Aves. A view of the Brooklyn Yacht Club, still in existence in 1908.

About 1900.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Twenty Third Ave., west side, between Cropsey and Warehouse Aves., showing the Royal Arcanum Yacht Club, and the Brooklyn Yacht Club at the left and right respectively.

About 1900.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Twenty Third Ave., south side, between Warehouse and Cropsey Aves.
April 27, 1935.

P. L. Sperr.

Warehouse Ave. (in foreground along water line) between 23rd (left) and 24th Aves. (right), showing from left to right the Goldenray apartments, at the N.E. corner of 23rd and Cropsey Ave; an old three story frame (white) in the line of Bay 34th Street, and the steeple of the Cropsey Ave. Methodist Church. At the right is the Cropsey and Mitchell Lumber Co.

P. L. Sperr.
